cs.LO, cs.LG, cs.PL, cs.AI, cs.FL

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper introduces a new logic, Parametric Linear Dynamic Logic (PLDL), and presents a translation of PLDL formulas into non-deterministic B\"uchi automata. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely category as the paper discusses model checking and optimization algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a possible category as the paper introduces a new logic and discusses its syntax and semantics. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper discusses algorithms for model checking and realizability, which are commonly used in AI. 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is a possible category as the paper discusses automata and their use in model checking and realizability.
